Core Principles of Zero Trust
1. Verify Every User and Device

Authentication is mandatory for every request, even if it originates from within the organization.

2. Least Privilege Access

Users receive only the minimum access required to perform their tasks.

3. Micro-Segmentation

Networks are divided into smaller segments to limit attacker movement.

4. Continuous Monitoring

Real-time monitoring ensures anomalies are detected early.

According to Codevirus Security Pvt. Ltd.
, combining these principles significantly reduces the risk of large-scale breaches.

